          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SURGT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Neutron induced fission cross sections are",
                "determined by the use of transfer reaction technique",
                "to measure the fission probability of neptunium",
                "formed in the reaction 238U(3He,t)238Np. The calculated",
                "compound nucleus formation cross section of a",
                "neutron-induced reaction is combined with the",
                "experimentally measured decay probability of the",
                "compound nucleus, produced via a surrogate reaction, to",
                "the desired exit channel to obtain the neutron-induced",
                "cross section indirectly.",
                "The compound nucleus formation cross section for the",
                "237Np+n was calculated for different incident neutron",
                "energies using the Flap2.2 optical-model potential.",
                " (see J.E.Escher and F.S.Dietrich, Tech. Rep.",
                "UCRL-TR-212509, Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory,",
                "                              Livermore, CA (2005)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "EN-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Uncertainty of excitation energy. The",
                "sources of uncertainty for the neutron energy were",
                "the energy straggle of the triton, angular",
                "resolution, beam energy resolution and detector",
                "resolution."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Statistical uncertainty. The statistical",
                "uncertainty for the fission events in each 120-keV",
                "energy bin was between 1 and 3%."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
